# Test commands (agents)

On Windows, `vendor\bin\phpunit` has no `.exe` extension. Invoking it directly opens a "choose app" dialog instead of running tests.

**Never** use `vendor/bin/phpunit` or `vendor\bin\phpunit` in shell commands.

**Never** run `docker compose … run composer vue:check` — the `composer` image has no npm. Use the `vue` service or `scripts/vue-check.ps1`.

## PHP

| Context | Command |
|---------|---------|
| Full PHP gate (Windows) | `.\scripts\check.ps1` — validate + PHPStan + PHPUnit + PHPCS in Docker |
| PHP + Vue gate | `.\scripts\check.ps1 -Vue` |
| PHPUnit only (Windows) | `.\scripts\test.ps1` — Docker by default |
| Single test file | `.\scripts\test.ps1 tests/Unit/SomeTest.php` |
| Host PHP 8.2+ (optional) | `.\scripts\test.ps1 -Local` |
| Docker (explicit) | `docker compose --profile tools run --rm composer check` |
| PHPCS only | `docker compose --profile tools run --rm composer phpcs` |
| PHP coverage (exploratory) | `.\scripts\coverage.ps1` — PCOV in Docker; see `docs/TEST_COVERAGE.md` |

## Vue

| Context | Command |
|---------|---------|
| Full Vue gate (Windows) | `.\scripts\vue-check.ps1` — typecheck + Vitest + build + verify in Docker |
| Host Node (optional) | `.\scripts\vue-check.ps1 -Local` |
| Docker (explicit) | `docker compose --profile tools run --rm vue sh -c "npm ci && npm run check"` |
| Build only (Docker) | `docker compose --profile tools run --rm vue sh -c "npm ci && npm run build && npm run verify"` |

`scripts/test.ps1`, `scripts/check.ps1`, and `scripts/vue-check.ps1` use Docker by default. Same codebase via volume mount.

See `docs/PHP_INSTALL_WINDOWS.md` and `docs/DEVELOPER.md` for humans.
